      "message": "nit: \"fewer\"\n\nIs this true? In a lot of APIs, you can request resources from the server, but it may opt to send you fewer than those that you requested. I would explicitly check the \"Next\" pointer here to see what it offers rather than expecting the server to behave. You could replace \"Log\" with \"logImpl\" and have it return a \"next\" string, and rewrite \"Log\" as a thin wrapper around it that discards that return value.",
